Class MolecularAction

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nlm.meme.action.LoggedAction.Default
      gov.nih.nlm.meme.action.MolecularAction
All Implemented Interfaces:
LoggedAction
Direct Known Subclasses:
MacroMolecularAction, MolecularAction, MolecularApproveConceptAction, MolecularChangeAtomAction, MolecularChangeAttributeAction, MolecularChangeConceptAction, MolecularChangeRelationshipAction, MolecularDeleteAtomAction, MolecularDeleteAttributeAction, MolecularDeleteConceptAction, MolecularDeleteRelationshipAction, MolecularInsertAtomAction, MolecularInsertAttributeAction, MolecularInsertConceptAction, MolecularInsertRelationshipAction, MolecularMergeAction, MolecularMoveAction, MolecularSplitAction
public class MolecularAction
extends LoggedAction.Default

Generically represents a molecular action and is typically has a MolecularTransaction as a parent and one or more AtomicActions as children. There is a contract for using a molecular action. It requires that applications instantiating actions (for use in the MID) must set the work identifier, transaction identifierd, authority, integrity vector, the change status flag, and the source/target concepts. Subclasses may have specific additional requirements.

Author:
MEME Group
